<topic id="component_customization_example">
  <title>Example - Customizing the DITA Framework</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Oxygen XML Author Component<indexterm>Customization<indexterm>Customize
              frameworks</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>If you look inside the <filepath>bundle-frameworks\oxygen-frameworks</filepath> folder
      distributed with the <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/oxygen_sdk.html#oXygen_standalone_applet_integration"
        format="html" scope="external"><ph keyref="authorComponent"/> sample project</xref>, it
      contains a <filepath>frameworks</filepath> folder. Customizations that affect the
        <term>framework</term> configuration for the component should first be done in a standalone
      installation of <ph keyref="product"/>.</p>
    <p>The <ph keyref="product"/> installation also includes a <filepath>frameworks</filepath>
      folder that contains the <filepath>dita</filepath>
      <term>framework</term> located in <filepath><term
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>\frameworks\dita</filepath>. The
        <filepath>dita</filepath>
      <term>framework</term> contains a bundled <b>DITA-OT</b> distribution that contains the DTDs
      used for DITA editing. If your DTD specialization is a DITA-OT plugin, it <xref
        href="howto-install-plugins.dita">should be installed</xref> in the <filepath><term
          keyref="glossentry_dita_ot_dir"/>\plugins</filepath> folder. </p>
    <p>To make changes to the DITA <term>framework</term> configuration, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to
        <uicontrol>Document Type Association</uicontrol>, and edit or extend the framework. These
      changes will affect the <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
        />\frameworks\dita\dita.framework</filepath> configuration file. </p>
    <p>After you do this, you can re-pack the <ph keyref="authorComponent"/> following the
      instructions from the README.html file located in the <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/oxygen_sdk.html#oXygen_standalone_applet_integration"
        format="html" scope="external"><ph keyref="authorComponent"/> sample project</xref>. The
        <i>Author Component</i> sample project and the <ph keyref="product"/> standalone
      installation should be of the same version. </p>
  </body>
